HEADWORD: Bridge-ward
<hw>Bridge"-ward`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
bridge keeper; a warden or a guard for a bridge.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The principal ward of a key.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bridgeing</ent>⟦br⟧
